<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="359" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1220,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1327,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The presence of bicuspid teeth in the outer rows on both the upper and lower jaws and a moderately sloped vomer block (48° in 
<typeStatus box="[464,564,1364,1389]" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">holotype</typeStatus>
) with a swollen rostral tip place this species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[1095,1233,1364,1389]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1095,1233,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">Metriaclima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male and female 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,272,1401,1424]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usisyae">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1401,1424]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. usisyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished by an elongate body (BD 25.9–30.6% SL) from all the other species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[1297,1435,1399,1424]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1297,1435,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">Metriaclima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BD 28.8–40.8% SL) except 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[513,646,1436,1461]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tarakiki">
<emphasis box="[513,646,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. tarakiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BD 25.8–32.9% SL) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[991,1155,1436,1461]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavicauda">
<emphasis box="[991,1155,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. flavicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BD 23.6–28.5% SL). 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,380,1471,1496]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usisyae">
<emphasis box="[151,380,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">Metriaclima usisyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[531,656,1471,1496]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tarakiki">
<emphasis box="[531,656,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. tarakiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a smaller eye, VED 23.1–28.1% HL vs. VED 30.2–36.5% HL in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,275,1508,1533]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tarakiki">
<emphasis box="[151,275,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. tarakiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and a shorter lower jaw length, LJL 29.9–33.4% HL vs. LJL 34.8–38.9% HL in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[1193,1318,1508,1533]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tarakiki">
<emphasis box="[1193,1318,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. tarakiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the color pattern, male 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[407,527,1545,1568]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usisyae">
<emphasis box="[407,527,1545,1568]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. usisyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess a yellow dorsal fin with a black submarginal band, yellow pelvic fins and yellow anal fin with a black leading edge. Male 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[685,840,1580,1605]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavicauda">
<emphasis box="[685,840,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. flavicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess black pelvic and anal fins, and a black dorsal fin with yellow/orange spots distally. The ground coloration of male 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[926,1082,1615,1640]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavicauda">
<emphasis box="[926,1082,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. flavicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is blue with 2 light blue/purple interorbital bars vs. yellow with 2 white/light blue interorbital bars in male 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[1035,1159,1653,1676]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usisyae">
<emphasis box="[1035,1159,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. usisyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[1313,1437,1653,1676]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usisyae">
<emphasis box="[1313,1437,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. usisyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot reliably be distinguished by color from those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[813,973,1687,1712]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavicauda">
<emphasis box="[813,836,1689,1712]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[855,973,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">flavicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[991,1259,1687,1712]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavicauda">
<emphasis box="[991,1259,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">Metriaclima flavicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also possess a deeper preorbital bone (
<collectionCode box="[422,475,1724,1748]" country="South Africa" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15547" name="South African National Biodiversity Institute (SANBI)" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">PRE</collectionCode>
18.0–26.9% HL) and a longer snout (SNL 34.3–47.3% HL), which are 17.6–21.2% and 32.0–37.6% in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[369,489,1761,1784]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usisyae">
<emphasis box="[369,489,1761,1784]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">M. usisyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="360" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1220,2037]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="360" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1796,1821]" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">Description.</emphasis>
Morphometric and meristic data in 
<tableCitation box="[750,837,1796,1821]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1382,234,1992]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 2. Morphological and meristic data for Metriaclima usisyae from Usisya, Lake Malaŵi, PSU 12759, holotype; PSU 12760, n = 14. Ranges include holotype." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4E76E1FF8BCC0BFF1EFF12EC5AE5E0" pageId="6" pageNumber="359" tableUuid="DF4E76E1FF8BCC0BFF1EFF12EC5AE5E0">Table 2</tableCitation>
. Elongate species (BD 25.9–30.6% SL) with greatest body depth at base of seventh or eighth dorsal-fin spine. Dorsal body profile with gradual curve to caudal peduncle with highest point at seventh or eighth dorsal-fin spine (greater body depth in males (mean BD 28.9% SL) than in females (mean BD 28.2% SL)); ventral body profile between pelvic and anal fins flat with upward curve to caudal fin. Dorsal head profile straight to slightly concave between snout tip and interorbital area, making 40–50° (45.5° in 
<typeStatus box="[179,279,1976,2001]" pageId="6" pageNumber="359">holotype</typeStatus>
) angle with body axis (greater angle in males than females), then round to dorsal-fin origin. Snout short with isognathic jaws. Teeth on lower jaw in 3–4 rows; upper jaw in 3–4 rows; outer rows bicuspid; inner rows tricuspid. First 3–4 dorsal-fin spines gradually longer posteriorly with first spine less than half length of fourth spine. Last dorsal-fin spine slightly longer than fourth spine. Soft dorsal fin with subacuminate tip, third or fourth ray longest, to about base of caudal fin in both males and females. Pectoral fin rounded, paddle-shaped. First ray of pelvic fin longer than other rays. Anal fin with 3 spines progressively longer posteriorly; third or fourth ray longest, length beyond base of caudal fin in males and to base of caudal fin in females. Caudal fin subtruncate to emarginate.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263003/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="360" targetBox="[151,1436,437,1340]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1365,1418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1365,1387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[289,500,1365,1387]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usisyae">
<emphasis box="[289,500,1365,1387]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">Metriaclima usisyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A. Holotype, PSU 12759, adult male, 74.8 mm SL, Usisya, Lake Malaŵi; B. Male in breeding coloration (approx. 70 mm SL) at type locality; C. Female (approx. 58 mm SL) at type locality.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1498,1991]" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">Lateral scales large, ctenoid; small cycloid scales on breast and belly; cheek with 5 rows of small scales. Dorsal fin and anal fin with narrow proximal band of tiny scales; tiny scales from base to 50% length of caudal fin.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1498,1991]" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">
Color notes and photos of live breeding adults (
<accessionNumber box="[762,900,1570,1595]" httpUri="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/PSU12761" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">
<collectionCode box="[762,815,1571,1595]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/5mg9-yyc1" name="Portland State University, Vertebrate Biology Museum" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">PSU</collectionCode>
12761
</accessionNumber>
). Males in territorial color with brown/yellow ground coloration and faint light brown bars. Head brown with 2 light blue/white interorbital bars and purple highlights; throat light blue. Dorsal fin black/yellow proximally, black distally with light blue lappets. Anal fin dark blue with 5–6 yellow ocelli and black/blue margin. Pectoral-fin rays brown with clear membranes (
<figureCitation box="[1262,1329,1678,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1365,1387]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1340]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,411,1341]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Metriaclima usisyae. A. Holotype, PSU 12759, adult male, 74.8 mm SL, Usisya, Lake Malaŵi; B. Male in breeding coloration (approx. 70 mm SL) at type locality; C. Female (approx. 58 mm SL) at type locality." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263003/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1498,1991]" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">
Females with brown ground coloration and 2–3 faint dark brown bars with purple/blue highlights on edge of scales. Belly and breast beige/brown. Head dark brown; black/gray opercular spot; interorbital bars purple/brown. Dorsal fin yellow/light brown proximally and black distally. Pectoral fin and pelvic fin brown/purple. Caudal fin light brown with dark brown ventral and dorsal margins (
<figureCitation box="[793,859,1822,1847]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1365,1387]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,437,1340]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,411,1341]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Metriaclima usisyae. A. Holotype, PSU 12759, adult male, 74.8 mm SL, Usisya, Lake Malaŵi; B. Male in breeding coloration (approx. 70 mm SL) at type locality; C. Female (approx. 58 mm SL) at type locality." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263003/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="360">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
